(A x B) Δ B = {(1, 2), (1, 3), (2, 2), (2, 3)} Δ {2, 3}

Since none of the elements in B are in (A x B), the symmetric difference is just the union of the two sets:

(A x B) Δ B = {(1, 2), (1, 3), (2, 2), (2, 3)}

